column5: Has anyone stayed here and fished this section of LOTW? How about their remote walk-in lakes? Any thoughts would be great or if you would prefer I PM you that is fine too. Thanks in advance
Stayed? No. But fished this area lots. I have a cottage about 20 minutes north. Fantastic walleye fishing, and far enough from Kenora etc that you avoid crowds.
2nd that......Fish the area every year.....Almost no pressure.....only 2 lodges within a good boat ride at all....Its an excellent area with great walleye, SM and muskie....
Nicko - what is the other lodge (besides Crow Rock) in this area of LOTW ? thanks, Rich
Wiley Point is not too far away.
Pipestone Point Resort and Moore Bay Lodge are not to far away from Crow Rock
Not far past Wiley is Big Narrows resort. Sent from my SM-N910W8 using Tapatalk
